6624
05:15:15,930 --> 05:15:19,319
with the Neuralink system, we
implant the Neuralink system

6625
05:15:19,319 --> 05:15:21,630
or the Neuralink implant
in the motor cortex.

6626
05:15:21,630 --> 05:15:22,799
So the motor cortex is responsible

6627
05:15:22,799 --> 05:15:25,829
for representing things like motor intent,

6628
05:15:25,830 --> 05:15:28,140
sort of if you imagine
closing and opening your hand,

6629
05:15:28,139 --> 05:15:29,220
that kind of signal representation

6630
05:15:29,220 --> 05:15:31,409
would be present in the motor cortex.

6631
05:15:31,409 --> 05:15:33,419
If you imagine moving
your arm back and forth

6632
05:15:33,419 --> 05:15:35,339
or wiggling a pinky, this sort of signal

6633
05:15:35,340 --> 05:15:37,139
can be present in the motor cortex.

6634
05:15:37,139 --> 05:15:39,540
So one of the ways we
start to sort of map out,

6635
05:15:39,540 --> 05:15:41,400
what kind of signal do we
actually have access to

6636
05:15:41,400 --> 05:15:42,870
in any particular individual's brain

6637
05:15:42,869 --> 05:15:44,819
is through this task called body mapping.

6638
05:15:44,819 --> 05:15:46,500
And body mapping is where
you essentially present

6639
05:15:46,500 --> 05:15:47,437
a visual to the user and you say,

6640
05:15:47,437 --> 05:15:49,620
"Hey, imagine doing this."

6641
05:15:49,619 --> 05:15:53,129
And that visual is a 3D
hand opening and closing,

6642
05:15:53,130 --> 05:15:55,710
or index finger modulating up and down.

6643
05:15:55,709 --> 05:15:57,419
And you ask the user to imagine that,

6644
05:15:57,419 --> 05:15:58,666
and obviously, you can't see them do this,

6645
05:15:58,667 --> 05:16:00,810
'cause they're paralyzed
so you can't see them

6646
05:16:00,810 --> 05:16:03,507
actually move their arm,
but while they do this task,

6647
05:16:03,507 --> 05:16:05,670
you can record neural activity,

6648
05:16:05,669 --> 05:16:07,919
and you can basically
offline model and check,

6649
05:16:07,919 --> 05:16:10,469
can I predict or can I
detect the modulation

6650
05:16:10,470 --> 05:16:12,360
corresponding with
those different actions?

6651
05:16:12,360 --> 05:16:13,740
And so we did that task and we realized,

6652
05:16:13,740 --> 05:16:15,480
hey, there's actually some modulation

6653
05:16:15,479 --> 05:16:17,159
associated with some of his hand motion,

6654
05:16:17,159 --> 05:16:18,930
which was the first indication that, okay,

6655
05:16:18,930 --> 05:16:20,400
we can potentially use that modulation

6656
05:16:20,400 --> 05:16:22,290
to do useful things in the world.

6657
05:16:22,290 --> 05:16:24,330
For example, control a computer cursor.

6658
05:16:24,330 --> 05:16:26,250
And he started playing with it,

6659
05:16:26,250 --> 05:16:27,180
the first time we showed him it,

6660
05:16:27,180 --> 05:16:28,680
and we actually just
took the same live view

6661
05:16:28,680 --> 05:16:30,689
