9218
06:49:13,500 --> 06:49:16,110
with no feeling from the shoulders down.

9219
06:49:16,110 --> 06:49:17,897
How did that accident change your life?

9220
06:49:17,897 --> 06:49:21,120
- That's sort of a freak
thing that happened.

9221
06:49:21,119 --> 06:49:25,289
Imagine you're running into the ocean,

9222
06:49:25,290 --> 06:49:28,080
although this is a lake, but
you're running into the ocean

9223
06:49:28,080 --> 06:49:30,300
and you get to about waist high,

9224
06:49:30,299 --> 06:49:32,489
and then you kind of like dive in,

9225
06:49:32,490 --> 06:49:35,010
take the rest of the plunge
under the wave or something.

9226
06:49:35,009 --> 06:49:36,689
That's what I did.

9227
06:49:36,689 --> 06:49:38,849
And then I just never came back up.

9228
06:49:38,849 --> 06:49:41,309
Not sure what happened.

9229
06:49:41,310 --> 06:49:44,880
I did it running into the
water with a couple of guys.

9230
06:49:44,880 --> 06:49:48,360
And so my idea of what happened

9231
06:49:48,360 --> 06:49:53,360
is really just that I
took like a stray fist,

9232
06:49:53,819 --> 06:49:57,810
elbow, knee, foot, something
to the side of my head.

9233
06:49:57,810 --> 06:49:59,700
The left side of my head was sore

9234
06:49:59,700 --> 06:50:01,500
for about a month afterwards.

9235
06:50:01,500 --> 06:50:03,779
So must must've taken a pretty big knock.

9236
06:50:03,779 --> 06:50:06,779
And then they both came up, and I didn't.

9237
06:50:06,779 --> 06:50:09,419
And so I was face down
in the water for a while.

9238
06:50:09,419 --> 06:50:10,893
I was conscious.

9239
06:50:12,389 --> 06:50:15,479
And then eventually just realized

9240
06:50:15,479 --> 06:50:16,709
I couldn't hold my breath any longer.

9241
06:50:16,709 --> 06:50:19,826
And I keep saying, "Took a big drink."

9242
06:50:20,819 --> 06:50:23,810
People, I don't know if
they like that I say that.

9243
06:50:23,810 --> 06:50:25,350
It seems like I'm making light of it all,

9244
06:50:25,349 --> 06:50:28,529
but it's just kind of how I am.

9245
06:50:28,529 --> 06:50:33,529
And I don't know, like I'm a very relaxed

9246
06:50:36,810 --> 06:50:39,569
sort of stress-free person.

9247
06:50:39,569 --> 06:50:44,143
I rolled with the punches
for a lot of this.

9248
06:50:44,143 --> 06:50:45,810
I kind of took it in stride.

9249
06:50:45,810 --> 06:50:47,729
It's like, "All right,
well what can I do next?

9250
06:50:47,729 --> 06:50:50,439
How can I improve my
life even a little bit

9251
06:50:51,360 --> 06:50:52,650
on a day-to-day basis?"

9252
06:50:52,650 --> 06:50:55,680
At first, just trying
to find some way to heal

9253
06:50:55,680 --> 06:50:57,393
as much of my body as possible,

9254
06:50:58,889 --> 06:51:02,489
to try to get healed, to
try to get off a ventilator,

9255
06:51:02,490 --> 06:51:07,490
learn as much as I could
so I could somehow survive

9256
06:51:09,990 --> 06:51:11,403
once I left the hospital.

9257
06:51:12,810 --> 06:51:17,040
And then thank God I had
like my family around me.

9258
06:51:17,040 --> 06:51:21,540
If I didn't have my parents, my siblings,

9259
06:51:21,540 --> 06:51:24,000
then I would've never made it this far.

9260
06:51:24,000 --> 06:51:26,639
They've done so much for me,

9261
06:51:26,639 --> 06:51:31,380
more than like I can ever
thank them for, honestly.

9262
06:51:31,380 --> 06:51:33,090
And a lot of people don't have that.

9263
06:51:33,090 --> 06:51:35,159
A lot of people in my situation,

9264
06:51:35,159 --> 06:51:37,889
their families either aren't
capable of providing for them,

9265
06:51:37,889 --> 06:51:41,279
or honestly, just don't want to.

9266
06:51:41,279 --> 06:51:44,909
And so they get placed
somewhere in some sort of home.

9267
06:51:44,909 --> 06:51:47,310
So thankfully I had my family.

9268
06:51:47,310 --> 06:51:49,080
I have a great group of friends,

9269
06:51:49,080 --> 06:51:51,060
a great group of buddies from college

9270
06:51:51,060 --> 06:51:53,430
who have all rallied around me,

9271
06:51:53,430 --> 06:51:56,520
and we're all still incredibly close.

9272
06:51:56,520 --> 06:51:58,409
People always say, "If you're lucky,

9273
06:51:58,409 --> 06:52:02,400
you'll end up with one or
two friends from high school

9274
06:52:02,400 --> 06:52:04,530
that you keep throughout your life."

9275
06:52:04,529 --> 06:52:08,789
I have about 10 or 12 from high school

9276
06:52:08,790 --> 06:52:10,380
that have all stuck around,

9277
06:52:10,380 --> 06:52:14,159
and we still get together,
all of us twice a year.

9278
06:52:14,159 --> 06:52:17,340
We call it the spring
series and the fall series.

9279
06:52:17,340 --> 06:52:21,119
This last one we all did,
we dressed up like X-Men.

9280
06:52:21,119 --> 06:52:25,529
So I did a Professor Xavier,
and it was freaking awesome.

9281
06:52:25,529 --> 06:52:27,149
It was so good.

9282
06:52:27,150 --> 06:52:29,370
So yeah, I have such a great
support system around me.

9283
06:52:29,369 --> 06:52:33,809
And so being a quadriplegic
isn't that bad.

9284
06:52:33,810 --> 06:52:37,110
I get waited on all the time.

9285
06:52:37,110 --> 06:52:41,040
People bring me food and
drinks, and I get to sit around

9286
06:52:41,040 --> 06:52:45,479
and watch as much TV and
movies and anime as I want.

9287
06:52:45,479 --> 06:52:47,733
I get to read as much as I want.

9288
06:52:49,139 --> 06:52:51,419
I mean, it's great.

9289
06:52:51,419 --> 06:52:52,799
- It's beautiful to see that

9290
06:52:52,799 --> 06:52:56,700
you see the silver lining in all of this.

9291
06:52:56,700 --> 06:52:59,340
Just going back, do
you remember the moment

9292
06:52:59,340 --> 06:53:01,830
when you first realized you were paralyzed

9293
06:53:01,830 --> 06:53:04,230
from the neck down?
- Yeah, yep.

9294
06:53:04,229 --> 06:53:06,159
I was face down in the water

9295
06:53:07,139 --> 06:53:10,049
right when whatever something hit my head.

9296
06:53:10,049 --> 06:53:14,309
I tried to get up and I
realized I couldn't move

9297
06:53:14,310 --> 06:53:16,363
and it just sort of clicked.

9298
06:53:16,363 --> 06:53:17,639
I'm like, "All right, I'm paralyzed.

9299
06:53:17,639 --> 06:53:18,630
Can't move.

9300
06:53:18,630 --> 06:53:19,563
What do I do?

9301
06:53:20,712 --> 06:53:23,099
If I can't get up, I can't flip over,

9302
06:53:23,099 --> 06:53:26,906
can't do anything, then I'm
gonna drown eventually."

9303
06:53:28,110 --> 06:53:30,330
And I knew I couldn't
hold my breath forever,

9304
06:53:30,330 --> 06:53:34,890
so I just held my breath
and thought about it

9305
06:53:34,889 --> 06:53:37,860
for maybe 10, 15 seconds.

9306
06:53:37,860 --> 06:53:41,430
I've heard from other people
that like look on liquors,

9307
06:53:41,430 --> 06:53:44,520
I guess the two girls that
pulled me out of the water

9308
06:53:44,520 --> 06:53:45,630
were two of my best friends.

9309
06:53:45,630 --> 06:53:46,712
They're lifeguards.

9310
06:53:48,090 --> 06:53:51,900
And one of them said that
it looked like my body

9311
06:53:51,900 --> 06:53:53,430
was sort of shaking in the water,

9312
06:53:53,430 --> 06:53:55,683
like I was trying to flip over and stuff.

9313
06:53:57,569 --> 06:53:59,759
But I knew, I knew immediately.

9314
06:53:59,759 --> 06:54:02,669
And I just kind of,

9315
06:54:02,669 --> 06:54:07,619
I realized that that's
what my situation was

9316
06:54:07,619 --> 06:54:08,729
from here on out.

9317
06:54:08,729 --> 06:54:10,020
Maybe if I got to the hospital,

9318
06:54:10,020 --> 06:54:11,490
they'd be able to do something.

9319
06:54:11,490 --> 06:54:12,690
When I was in the hospital,

9320
06:54:12,689 --> 06:54:14,159
like right before surgery,

9321
06:54:14,159 --> 06:54:17,819
I was trying to calm
one of my friends down.

9322
06:54:17,819 --> 06:54:20,700
I had like brought her with
me from college to camp,

9323
06:54:20,700 --> 06:54:22,566
and she was just bawling
over me, and I was like,

9324
06:54:22,566 --> 06:54:23,819
"Hey, it's gonna be fine.

9325
06:54:23,819 --> 06:54:25,709
Like don't worry."

9326
06:54:25,709 --> 06:54:28,919
I was cracking some jokes
to try to lighten the mood.

9327
06:54:28,919 --> 06:54:30,636
The nurse had called
my mom, and I was like,

9328
06:54:30,636 --> 06:54:32,399
"Don't tell my mom.

9329
06:54:32,400 --> 06:54:34,020
She's just gonna be stressed out.

9330
06:54:34,020 --> 06:54:36,090
Call her after I'm out of surgery,"

9331
06:54:36,090 --> 06:54:38,040
'cause at least she'll
have some answers then,

9332
06:54:38,040 --> 06:54:40,473
like whether I live or not, really.

9333
06:54:41,490 --> 06:54:43,050
And I didn't want her to be stressed

9334
06:54:43,049 --> 06:54:44,189
through the whole thing.

9335
06:54:44,189 --> 06:54:45,022
But I knew.

9336
06:54:45,023 --> 06:54:48,299
And then when I first
woke up after surgery,

9337
06:54:48,299 --> 06:54:50,369
I was super drugged up.

9338
06:54:50,369 --> 06:54:54,828
They had me on fentanyl like
three ways, which was awesome.

9339
06:54:54,829 --> 06:54:59,829
I don't recommend it, but
I saw some crazy stuff

9340
06:55:01,560 --> 06:55:03,540
on that fentanyl, and it was still

9341
06:55:03,540 --> 06:55:06,273
the best I've ever felt on drugs.

9342
06:55:07,529 --> 06:55:09,692
Medication, sorry, on medication.

9343
06:55:11,250 --> 06:55:15,209
And I remember the first time
I saw my mom in the hospital.

9344
06:55:15,209 --> 06:55:16,649
I was just bawling.

9345
06:55:16,650 --> 06:55:20,010
I had like ventilator in,

9346
06:55:20,009 --> 06:55:21,959
like I couldn't talk or anything,

9347
06:55:21,959 --> 06:55:24,779
and I just started crying,

9348
06:55:24,779 --> 06:55:26,733
because it was more like seeing her.

9349
06:55:28,290 --> 06:55:31,799
I mean, the whole situation
obviously was pretty rough,

9350
06:55:31,799 --> 06:55:33,750
but it was just like seeing her face

9351
06:55:33,750 --> 06:55:35,610
for the first time was pretty hard.

9352
06:55:35,610 --> 06:55:40,610
But yeah, I never had like a moment of,

9353
06:55:42,487 --> 06:55:45,540
"Man, I'm paralyzed.

9354
06:55:45,540 --> 06:55:46,372
This sucks.

9355
06:55:46,372 --> 06:55:48,509
I don't wanna like be around anymore."

9356
06:55:48,509 --> 06:55:52,649
It was always just, "I hate
that I have to do this,

9357
06:55:52,650 --> 06:55:57,030
but like sitting here and
wallowing isn't gonna help."

9358
06:55:57,029 --> 06:55:58,860
- So immediate acceptance.

9359
06:55:58,860 --> 06:56:01,170
- [Noland] Yeah, yeah.

9360
06:56:01,169 --> 06:56:03,539
- Has there been low points along the way?

9361
06:56:03,540 --> 06:56:04,802
- Yeah, yeah, sure.

9362
06:56:06,180 --> 06:56:09,000
I mean, there are days
when I don't really feel

9363
06:56:09,000 --> 06:56:10,169
like doing anything.

9364
06:56:10,169 --> 06:56:11,579
Not so much anymore.

9365
06:56:11,580 --> 06:56:13,140
Like not for the last couple years,

9366
06:56:13,139 --> 06:56:14,399
I don't really feel that way.

9367
06:56:14,400 --> 06:56:19,400
I've more so just wanted to
try to do anything possible

9368
06:56:21,240 --> 06:56:24,300
to make my life better at this point.

9369
06:56:24,299 --> 06:56:26,790
But at the beginning, there
were some ups and downs.

9370
06:56:26,790 --> 06:56:29,190
There were some really
hard things to adjust to.

9371
06:56:30,450 --> 06:56:32,490
First off, just like
the first couple months,

9372
06:56:32,490 --> 06:56:35,513
the amount of pain I was
in was really, really hard.

9373
06:56:35,512 --> 06:56:38,430
I mean, I remember screaming

9374
06:56:38,430 --> 06:56:40,319
at the top of my lungs in the hospital,

9375
06:56:40,319 --> 06:56:42,419
because I thought my legs were on fire.

9376
06:56:42,419 --> 06:56:44,729
And obviously, I can't feel anything,

9377
06:56:44,729 --> 06:56:46,290
but it's all nerve pain.

9378
06:56:46,290 --> 06:56:48,209
And so that was a really hard night.

9379
06:56:48,209 --> 06:56:51,029
I asked them to give me as
much pain meds as possible.

9380
06:56:51,029 --> 06:56:53,309
They're like, "You've had
as much as you can have,

9381
06:56:53,310 --> 06:56:55,020
so just kind of deal with it.

9382
06:56:55,020 --> 06:56:56,700
Go to a happy place sort of thing."

9383
06:56:56,700 --> 06:56:58,250
So that was a pretty low point.

9384
06:56:59,159 --> 06:57:01,110
And then every now and again, it's hard,

9385
06:57:01,110 --> 06:57:04,889
like realizing things that
I wanted to do in my life

9386
06:57:04,889 --> 06:57:06,639
that I won't be able to do anymore.

9387
06:57:08,159 --> 06:57:11,250
I always wanted to be
a husband and father,

9388
06:57:11,250 --> 06:57:13,919
and I just don't think
that I could do it now

9389
06:57:13,919 --> 06:57:14,819
as a quadriplegic.

9390
06:57:14,819 --> 06:57:17,590
Maybe it's possible, but
I'm not sure I would ever

9391
06:57:18,689 --> 06:57:22,052
put someone I love through that,

9392
06:57:23,130 --> 06:57:25,180
like having to take care of me and stuff.

9393
06:57:26,340 --> 06:57:29,220
Not being able to go out and play sports.

9394
06:57:29,220 --> 06:57:32,883
I was a huge athlete growing
up, so that was pretty hard.

9395
06:57:33,779 --> 06:57:37,139
Little things too, when I
realized I can't do them anymore.

9396
06:57:37,139 --> 06:57:40,110
Like there's something really special

9397
06:57:40,110 --> 06:57:44,459
about being able to hold
a book and smell a book.

9398
06:57:44,459 --> 06:57:47,279
Like the feel, the texture, the smell,

9399
06:57:47,279 --> 06:57:49,619
like as you turn the
pages, like I just love it.

9400
06:57:49,619 --> 06:57:50,546
I can't do it anymore.

9401
06:57:50,546 --> 06:57:52,292
And it's little things like that.

9402
06:57:53,250 --> 06:57:55,619
The two-year mark was pretty rough.

9403
06:57:55,619 --> 06:58:00,619
Two years is when they say
you will get back basically

9404
06:58:02,490 --> 06:58:03,960
as much as you're ever gonna get back,

9405
06:58:03,959 --> 06:58:06,090
as far as movement and sensation goes.

9406
06:58:06,090 --> 06:58:07,560
And so for the first two years,

9407
06:58:07,560 --> 06:58:10,680
that was the only thing
on my mind was like

9408
06:58:10,680 --> 06:58:14,189
try as much as I can to move my fingers,

9409
06:58:14,189 --> 06:58:17,099
my hands, my feet, everything possible

9410
06:58:17,099 --> 06:58:19,079
to try to get sensation and movement back.

9411
06:58:19,080 --> 06:58:21,900
And then when the two-year mark hit,

9412
06:58:21,900 --> 06:58:26,133
so June 30th, 2018,

9413
06:58:28,066 --> 06:58:32,082
I was really sad that
that's kind of where I was.

9414
06:58:33,599 --> 06:58:35,430
And then just randomly here and there,

9415
06:58:35,430 --> 06:58:40,430
but I was never like depressed
for long periods of time.

9416
06:58:41,400 --> 06:58:45,930
Just it never seemed worthwhile to me.

9417
06:58:45,930 --> 06:58:47,670
- What gave you strength?

9418
06:58:47,669 --> 06:58:48,539
- My faith.

9419
06:58:48,540 --> 06:58:51,120
My faith in God was a big one.

9420
06:58:51,119 --> 06:58:54,270
My understanding that it
was all for a purpose.

9421
06:58:54,270 --> 06:58:57,029
And even if that purpose wasn't anything

9422
06:58:57,029 --> 06:58:59,882
involving Neuralink,
even if that purpose was,

9423
06:59:02,342 --> 06:59:05,137
there's a story in the Bible about Job,

9424
06:59:05,137 --> 06:59:07,169
and I think it's a really,
really popular story,

9425
06:59:07,169 --> 06:59:10,379
about how Job has all
of these terrible things

9426
06:59:10,380 --> 06:59:11,700
happen to him, and he praises God

9427
06:59:11,700 --> 06:59:14,310
throughout the whole situation.

9428
06:59:14,310 --> 06:59:17,610
I thought, and I think
a lot of people think

9429
06:59:17,610 --> 06:59:20,310
for most of their lives that they are Job,

9430
06:59:20,310 --> 06:59:22,890
that they're the ones going
through something terrible,

9431
06:59:22,889 --> 06:59:26,700
and they just need to praise
God through the whole thing

9432
06:59:26,700 --> 06:59:28,319
and everything will work out.

9433
06:59:28,319 --> 06:59:30,119
At some point after my accident,

9434
06:59:30,119 --> 06:59:33,869
I realized that I might not be Job,

9435
06:59:33,869 --> 06:59:36,869
that I might be one of his children

9436
06:59:36,869 --> 06:59:40,079
that gets killed or
kidnapped or taken from him.

9437
06:59:40,080 --> 06:59:44,220
And so it's about terrible
things that happen

9438
06:59:44,220 --> 06:59:45,930
to those around you who you love.

9439
06:59:45,930 --> 06:59:49,290
So maybe, in this case,
my mom would be Job,

9440
06:59:49,290 --> 06:59:54,000
and she has to get through
something extraordinarily hard

9441
06:59:54,000 --> 06:59:57,240
and I just need to try and make it

9442
06:59:57,240 --> 06:59:59,430
as best as possible for her,

9443
06:59:59,430 --> 07:00:02,369
because she's the one that's really

9444
07:00:02,369 --> 07:00:04,619
going through this massive trial.

9445
07:00:04,619 --> 07:00:06,450
And that gave me a lot of strength.

9446
07:00:06,450 --> 07:00:07,773
And obviously, my family.

9447
07:00:08,610 --> 07:00:10,200
My family and my friends,

9448
07:00:10,200 --> 07:00:13,590
they give me all the strength that I need

9449
07:00:13,590 --> 07:00:15,180
on a day-to-day basis.

9450
07:00:15,180 --> 07:00:17,189
So it makes things a lot easier

9451
07:00:17,189 --> 07:00:20,039
having that great
support system around me.

9452
07:00:20,040 --> 07:00:21,630
- From everything I've seen of you online,

9453
07:00:21,630 --> 07:00:26,630
your streams and the way you
are today, I really admire,

9454
07:00:26,909 --> 07:00:30,389
let's say, your unwavering
positive outlook on life.

9455
07:00:30,389 --> 07:00:32,489
Has that always been this way?

9456
07:00:32,490 --> 07:00:33,963
- Yeah, yeah.

9457
07:00:35,020 --> 07:00:37,847
I mean, I've just always thought

9458
07:00:39,569 --> 07:00:42,689
I could do anything I ever wanted to do.

9459
07:00:42,689 --> 07:00:44,699
There was never anything too big.

9460
07:00:44,700 --> 07:00:47,762
Like whatever I set my mind
to, I felt like I could do it.

9461
07:00:49,049 --> 07:00:52,469
I didn't wanna do a lot.

9462
07:00:52,470 --> 07:00:54,030
I wanted to like travel around

9463
07:00:54,029 --> 07:00:58,139
and be sort of like a gypsy
and like go work odd jobs.

9464
07:00:58,139 --> 07:01:00,689
I had this dream of
traveling around Europe

9465
07:01:00,689 --> 07:01:02,729
and being like, I don't know,

9466
07:01:02,729 --> 07:01:06,090
a shepherd in like Wales or Ireland.

9467
07:01:06,090 --> 07:01:09,180
And then going and being
a fisherman in Italy,

9468
07:01:09,180 --> 07:01:10,799
doing all these things for like a year.

9469
07:01:10,799 --> 07:01:13,110
Like it's such like cliche things,

9470
07:01:13,110 --> 07:01:14,970
but I just thought it would be so much fun

9471
07:01:14,970 --> 07:01:17,700
to go and travel and do different things.

9472
07:01:17,700 --> 07:01:21,930
And so I've always just seen

9473
07:01:21,930 --> 07:01:24,930
the best in people around me too.

9474
07:01:24,930 --> 07:01:28,500
And I've always tried
to be good to people.

9475
07:01:28,500 --> 07:01:31,349
And growing up with my mom too,

9476
07:01:31,349 --> 07:01:35,009
she's like the most positive
energetic person in the world.

9477
07:01:35,009 --> 07:01:37,262
And we're all just people people.

9478
07:01:38,310 --> 07:01:40,920
I just get along great with people.

9479
07:01:40,919 --> 07:01:42,719
I really enjoy meeting new people,

9480
07:01:42,720 --> 07:01:46,233
and so I just wanted to do everything.

9481
07:01:47,310 --> 07:01:50,430
This is just kind of just how I've been.

9482
07:01:50,430 --> 07:01:53,909
- It's just great to see that
cynicism didn't take over,

9483
07:01:53,909 --> 07:01:55,229
given everything you've been through.

9484
07:01:55,229 --> 07:01:56,819
- Yeah.

9485
07:01:56,819 --> 07:01:59,250
- Was that like a
deliberate choice you made

9486
07:01:59,250 --> 07:02:01,259
that you're not gonna
let this keep you down?

9487
07:02:01,259 --> 07:02:02,669
- Yeah, a bit.

9488
07:02:02,669 --> 07:02:06,422
Also, like it's just kind of how I am.

9489
07:02:07,560 --> 07:02:09,510
Like I said, I roll with
the punches with everything.

9490
07:02:09,509 --> 07:02:11,639
I always used to tell people,

9491
07:02:11,639 --> 07:02:15,149
like I don't stress about things much.

9492
07:02:15,150 --> 07:02:17,400
And whenever I'd see
people getting stressed,

9493
07:02:17,400 --> 07:02:19,560
I would just say, "It's not hard.

9494
07:02:19,560 --> 07:02:21,450
Just don't stress about it."

9495
07:02:21,450 --> 07:02:24,150
And that's all you need to do.

9496
07:02:24,150 --> 07:02:26,559
And they're like, "That's
not how that works."

9497
07:02:26,559 --> 07:02:27,391
I'm like, "It works for me.

9498
07:02:27,391 --> 07:02:30,150
Like just don't stress, and
everything will be fine.

9499
07:02:30,150 --> 07:02:31,290
Like everything will work out."

9500
07:02:31,290 --> 07:02:34,370
Obviously, not everything
always goes well,

9501
07:02:34,369 --> 07:02:35,610
and it's not like it all works out

9502
07:02:35,610 --> 07:02:37,650
for the best all the time,

9503
07:02:37,650 --> 07:02:40,740
but I just don't think stress has had

9504
07:02:40,740 --> 07:02:43,173
any place in my life since I was a kid.

9505
07:02:44,310 --> 07:02:46,050
- What was the experience like

9506
07:02:46,049 --> 07:02:49,770
of you being selected to
be the first human being

9507
07:02:49,770 --> 07:02:52,319
to have a Neuralink device
implanted in your brain?

9508
07:02:53,383 --> 07:02:56,144
Were you scared, excited?
- No, no, it was cool.

9509
07:02:56,144 --> 07:02:58,173
(Lex laughing)

9510
07:02:58,173 --> 07:03:01,649
Like I was never afraid of it.

9511
07:03:01,650 --> 07:03:03,798
I had to think through a lot.

9512
07:03:03,797 --> 07:03:07,469
Should I do this?

9513
07:03:07,470 --> 07:03:09,270
Like be the first person?

9514
07:03:09,270 --> 07:03:12,209
I could wait until number two or three

9515
07:03:12,209 --> 07:03:14,759
and get a better version of the Neuralink.

9516
07:03:14,759 --> 07:03:16,859
Like the first one might not work.

9517
07:03:16,860 --> 07:03:20,712
Maybe it's actually gonna kind of suck it.

9518
07:03:21,930 --> 07:03:24,720
It's gonna be the worst
version ever in a person.

9519
07:03:24,720 --> 07:03:26,580
So why would I do the first one?

9520
07:03:26,580 --> 07:03:27,990
Like I've already kind of been selected.

9521
07:03:27,990 --> 07:03:30,690
I could just tell them, like,
"Okay, find someone else,

9522
07:03:30,689 --> 07:03:31,859
and then I'll do number two or three."

9523
07:03:31,860 --> 07:03:33,209
Like I'm sure they would let me.

9524
07:03:33,209 --> 07:03:35,189
They're looking for a few people anyways.

9525
07:03:35,189 --> 07:03:37,079
But ultimately, I was like, I don't know,

9526
07:03:37,080 --> 07:03:39,330
there's something about being
the first one to do something.

9527
07:03:39,330 --> 07:03:40,260
It's pretty cool.

9528
07:03:40,259 --> 07:03:43,500
I always thought that if I had the chance

9529
07:03:43,500 --> 07:03:46,233
that I would like to do
something for the first time,

9530
07:03:47,189 --> 07:03:49,340
this seemed like a
pretty good opportunity,

9531
07:03:50,189 --> 07:03:51,779
and I was never scared.

9532
07:03:51,779 --> 07:03:56,779
I think my like faith
had a huge part in that.

9533
07:03:57,569 --> 07:04:01,863
I always felt like God was
preparing me for something.

9534
07:04:02,880 --> 07:04:05,940
I almost wish it wasn't this,

9535
07:04:05,939 --> 07:04:09,119
because I had many conversations with God

9536
07:04:09,119 --> 07:04:12,840
about not wanting to do any
of this as a quadriplegic.

9537
07:04:12,840 --> 07:04:15,540
I told him, "I'll go
out and talk to people.

9538
07:04:15,540 --> 07:04:17,670
I'll go out and travel the world

9539
07:04:17,669 --> 07:04:21,000
and talk to stadiums, thousands of people,

9540
07:04:21,000 --> 07:04:22,919
give my testimony, I'll do all of it,

9541
07:04:22,919 --> 07:04:24,569
but like heal me first.

9542
07:04:24,569 --> 07:04:26,220
Don't make me do all of this in a chair.

9543
07:04:26,220 --> 07:04:27,266
That sucks."

9544
07:04:28,500 --> 07:04:31,560
And I guess he won that argument.

9545
07:04:31,560 --> 07:04:33,720
I didn't really have much of a choice.

9546
07:04:33,720 --> 07:04:37,710
I always felt like there
was something going on.

9547
07:04:37,709 --> 07:04:42,709
And to see how, I guess,
easily I made it through

9548
07:04:45,240 --> 07:04:46,560
the interview process

9549
07:04:46,560 --> 07:04:49,023
and how quickly everything happened,

9550
07:04:50,130 --> 07:04:53,043
how the stars sort of
aligned with all of this,

9551
07:04:54,840 --> 07:04:58,200
it just told me like, as the
surgery was getting closer,

9552
07:04:58,200 --> 07:05:02,670
it just told me that it
was all meant to happen.

9553
07:05:02,669 --> 07:05:03,899
It was all meant to be.

9554
07:05:03,900 --> 07:05:07,347
And so I shouldn't be afraid
of anything that's to come.

9555
07:05:07,347 --> 07:05:08,670
And so I wasn't.

9556
07:05:08,669 --> 07:05:10,143
I kept telling myself like,

9557
07:05:11,226 --> 07:05:14,039
"You say that now, but as
soon as the surgery comes,

9558
07:05:14,040 --> 07:05:15,690
you're probably gonna be freaking out.

9559
07:05:15,689 --> 07:05:17,099
Like you're about to have brain surgery."

9560
07:05:17,099 --> 07:05:21,239
And brain surgery is a big
deal for a lot of people,

9561
07:05:21,240 --> 07:05:23,310
but it's a even bigger deal for me.

9562
07:05:23,310 --> 07:05:24,780
Like it's all I have left.

9563
07:05:24,779 --> 07:05:26,287
The amount of times I've been like,

9564
07:05:26,287 --> 07:05:28,470
"Thank you God that you
didn't take my brain

9565
07:05:28,470 --> 07:05:31,740
and my personality and
my ability to think,

9566
07:05:31,740 --> 07:05:33,390
my like love of learning,

9567
07:05:33,389 --> 07:05:35,970
like my character, everything,
like thank you so much.

9568
07:05:35,970 --> 07:05:38,069
Like as long as you left me that,

9569
07:05:38,069 --> 07:05:39,509
then I think I can get by."

9570
07:05:39,509 --> 07:05:43,559
And I was about to let
people go like root around,

9571
07:05:43,560 --> 07:05:45,510
and they're like, "Hey, we're gonna go

9572
07:05:45,509 --> 07:05:46,739
put some stuff in your brain.

9573
07:05:46,740 --> 07:05:47,990
Hopefully, it works out."

9574
07:05:49,229 --> 07:05:51,779
And so it was something
that gave me pause.

9575
07:05:51,779 --> 07:05:54,869
But like I said, how
smoothly everything went,

9576
07:05:54,869 --> 07:05:58,709
I never expected for a second
that anything would go wrong.

9577
07:05:58,709 --> 07:06:02,700
Plus, the more people I
met on the Barrow's side

9578
07:06:02,700 --> 07:06:04,590
and on the Neuralink side,

9579
07:06:04,590 --> 07:06:06,869
they're just the most
impressive people in the world.

9580
07:06:06,869 --> 07:06:10,289
Like I can't speak enough

9581
07:06:10,290 --> 07:06:13,139
to how much I trust
these people with my life

9582
07:06:13,139 --> 07:06:16,766
and how impressed I am with all of them.

9583
07:06:16,766 --> 07:06:19,470
And to see the excitement on their faces,

9584
07:06:19,470 --> 07:06:24,150
to like walk into a room
and roll into a room

9585
07:06:24,150 --> 07:06:26,700
and see all of these people looking at me,

9586
07:06:26,700 --> 07:06:28,500
like we're so excited.

9587
07:06:28,500 --> 07:06:30,750
Like we've been working so hard on this,

9588
07:06:30,750 --> 07:06:32,159
and it's finally happening.

9589
07:06:32,159 --> 07:06:34,079
It's super infectious,

9590
07:06:34,080 --> 07:06:37,350
and it just makes me wanna do it even more

9591
07:06:37,349 --> 07:06:39,989
and to help them achieve their dreams.

9592
07:06:39,990 --> 07:06:42,600
Like I don't know, it's so rewarding.

9593
07:06:42,599 --> 07:06:45,239
And I'm so happy for
all of them, honestly.

9594
07:06:45,240 --> 07:06:47,463
- What was the day of surgery like?

9595
07:06:48,750 --> 07:06:49,889
When did you wake up?

9596
07:06:49,889 --> 07:06:51,569
What'd you feel?

9597
07:06:51,569 --> 07:06:53,069
- Yeah.
- Minute by minute.

9598
07:06:53,069 --> 07:06:54,147
- Yeah.
- Were you freaking out?

9599
07:06:54,147 --> 07:06:55,709
- No, no.

9600
07:06:55,709 --> 07:06:56,790
I thought I was going to,

9601
07:06:56,790 --> 07:06:59,130
but as surgery approached
the night before,

9602
07:06:59,130 --> 07:07:01,503
the morning of, I was just excited.

9603
07:07:02,610 --> 07:07:03,869
Let's make this happen.

9604
07:07:03,869 --> 07:07:06,450
I think I said something like that

9605
07:07:06,450 --> 07:07:08,549
to Elon on the phone beforehand.

9606
07:07:08,549 --> 07:07:10,319
We were like FaceTiming,

9607
07:07:10,319 --> 07:07:11,970
and I was like, "Let's rock and roll."

9608
07:07:11,970 --> 07:07:13,420
And he's like, "Let's do it."

9609
07:07:14,279 --> 07:07:16,829
I don't know, I wasn't scared.

9610
07:07:16,830 --> 07:07:17,760
So we woke up.

9611
07:07:17,759 --> 07:07:20,459
I think we had to be at the
hospital at like 5:30 AM.

9612
07:07:20,459 --> 07:07:22,709
I think surgery was at like 7:00 AM.

9613
07:07:22,709 --> 07:07:24,000
So we woke up pretty early.

9614
07:07:24,000 --> 07:07:27,122
I'm not sure much of us slept that night.

9615
07:07:30,209 --> 07:07:32,459
Got to the hospital 5:30,

9616
07:07:32,459 --> 07:07:35,669
went through like all the pre-op stuff.

9617
07:07:35,669 --> 07:07:37,799
Everyone was super nice.

9618
07:07:37,799 --> 07:07:40,380
Elon was supposed to be
there in the morning,

9619
07:07:40,380 --> 07:07:41,729
but something went wrong with his plane,

9620
07:07:41,729 --> 07:07:43,590
so we ended up FaceTiming.

9621
07:07:43,590 --> 07:07:44,422
That was cool.

9622
07:07:44,422 --> 07:07:47,159
Had one of the greatest
one-liners of my life.

9623
07:07:47,159 --> 07:07:49,590
After that phone call, hung up with him.

9624
07:07:49,590 --> 07:07:51,347
There were like 20 people
around me, and I was like,

9625
07:07:51,347 --> 07:07:54,420
I just hope he wasn't too
starstruck talking to me.

9626
07:07:54,419 --> 07:07:55,952
- Nice.
- Yeah, it was good.

9627
07:07:55,953 --> 07:07:57,690
- Well done.
- Yeah, yeah.

9628
07:07:57,689 --> 07:07:59,881
- Did you write that ahead of
time, or it just came to you?

9629
07:07:59,882 --> 07:08:00,873
- No, it just came to me.

9630
07:08:00,873 --> 07:08:03,537
I was like, "This seems right."

9631
07:08:04,799 --> 07:08:06,242
When in surgery,

9632
07:08:07,080 --> 07:08:09,480
I asked if I could pray right beforehand.

9633
07:08:09,479 --> 07:08:11,159
So I like prayed over the room.

9634
07:08:11,159 --> 07:08:13,439
I asked God if you would
like be with my mom

9635
07:08:13,439 --> 07:08:15,389
in case anything happened to me.

9636
07:08:15,389 --> 07:08:18,779
And just to like calm
her nerves out there.

9637
07:08:18,779 --> 07:08:22,979
Woke up and played a bit
of a prank on my mom.

9638
07:08:22,979 --> 07:08:23,992
I don't know if you've heard about it.

9639
07:08:23,992 --> 07:08:25,169
- Yeah, I read about it.

9640
07:08:25,169 --> 07:08:27,269
- Yeah, she was not happy.

9641
07:08:27,270 --> 07:08:29,400
- Can you take me through the prank

9642
07:08:29,400 --> 07:08:31,067
- Yeah, this is something-
- Do you regret

9643
07:08:31,066 --> 07:08:33,663
doing that now?
- No, no, not one bit.

9644
07:08:34,792 --> 07:08:37,950
It was something I had talked about

9645
07:08:37,950 --> 07:08:38,996
ahead of time with my buddy, Bain.

9646
07:08:38,996 --> 07:08:43,346
I was like, "I would really
like to play a prank on my mom."

9647
07:08:44,700 --> 07:08:46,260
Very specifically, my mom.

9648
07:08:46,259 --> 07:08:48,119
She's very gullible.

9649
07:08:48,119 --> 07:08:51,000
I think she had knee surgery once even.

9650
07:08:51,000 --> 07:08:54,122
And after she came out of knee surgery,

9651
07:08:55,709 --> 07:08:57,779
she was super groggy.

9652
07:08:57,779 --> 07:08:59,489
She's like, "I can't feel my legs."

9653
07:08:59,490 --> 07:09:01,387
And my dad looked at her, he was like,

9654
07:09:01,386 --> 07:09:02,699
"You don't have any legs.

9655
07:09:02,700 --> 07:09:05,787
Like they had to amputate both your legs."

9656
07:09:07,409 --> 07:09:11,092
We just do very mean
things to her all the time.

9657
07:09:11,092 --> 07:09:14,493
I'm so surprised that she still loves us.

9658
07:09:15,419 --> 07:09:18,196
But right after surgery,
I was really worried

9659
07:09:18,197 --> 07:09:22,080
that I was going to be too like
groggy, like not all there.

9660
07:09:22,080 --> 07:09:27,030
I had anesthesia once
before, and it messed me up.

9661
07:09:27,029 --> 07:09:30,809
Like I could not function
for a while afterwards.

9662
07:09:30,810 --> 07:09:35,400
And I like said a lot of
things that I was like,

9663
07:09:35,400 --> 07:09:38,159
I was really worried
that I was gonna start,

9664
07:09:38,159 --> 07:09:41,669
I don't know, like dropping some bombs.

9665
07:09:41,669 --> 07:09:44,759
And I wouldn't even know,
I wouldn't remember.

9666
07:09:44,759 --> 07:09:48,419
So I was like, "Please
God, don't let that happen.

9667
07:09:48,419 --> 07:09:52,556
And please let me be there
enough to do this to my mom."

9668
07:09:54,240 --> 07:09:58,140
And so she walked in after surgery.

